  "prompt": "What will be the derivative of x|x|, if x is -1",
  "response": "To find the derivative of \\( f(x) = x|x| \\) at \\( x = -1 \\), follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Understand the Function\nThe function \\( f(x) = x|x| \\) can be expressed piecewise based on the value of \\( x \\):\n\n\\[\nf(x) = \n\\begin{cases} \nx^2 & \\text{if } x \\geq 0 \\\\\n-x^2 & \\text{if } x < 0\n\\end{cases}\n\\]\n\n### 2. Compute the Derivative for Each Piece\n- **For \\( x \\geq 0 \\):**  \n  \\( f(x) = x^2 \\)  \n  \\( f'(x) = 2x \\)\n\n- **For \\( x < 0 \\):**  \n  \\( f(x) = -x^2 \\)  \n  \\( f'(x) = -2x \\)\n\n### 3. Evaluate the Derivative at \\( x = -1 \\)\nSince \\( x = -1 < 0 \\), we use the derivative for the \\( x < 0 \\) case:\n\n\\[\nf'(-1) = -2(-1) = 2\n\\]\n\n### Final Answer\n\\[\n\\boxed{2}\n\\]",
